# SyncForm conventions

## Layout

- Top bar: watermark DateTimePicker, Start Sync, mock checkbox, status.
- Tabs: Sync Log, Mapping, Settings.
- Mapping toolbar: Save Mappings, dirty label, Refresh Spesnet Reference Data, Refresh from Toggl.
- Prefer editing `SyncForm.Designer.cs` for control layout; keep async/event wiring in `SyncForm.cs`.
- Settings includes Data Directory (writes `config-location.json` on Save Settings; creates folder and missing config files; copies from previous data dir when the new folder lacks them).

## Mapping grid

- One grid: Status → Toggl client → Toggl project (filtered by client; empty allowed) → Spesnet project → Spesnet client → Spesnet work task.
- Status cell colors: Active=green, Ignore=blue, New=amber (painted on the closed combo cell via CellPainting).
- Auto-populate one row per live Toggl client+project on Refresh from Toggl; new pairs start as `New` and mark mappings dirty until Save.
- Client-only row (empty project) with Status=`Ignore` covers all projects for that client.
- Reload Toggl projects when the Toggl client combo changes; reload Spesnet clients when the Spesnet project combo changes.
- Persist mappings only via **Save Mappings** (explicit). Warn on close if dirty; block Start Sync while dirty.

## Behaviour

- Disable sync/refresh buttons while async work runs.
- Marshal logger UI updates with `Invoke`/`BeginInvoke` when needed.
- On load: restore watermark, settings, mappings; optionally auto-load Spesnet reference (especially mock).
- Require Spesnet reference cache; block sync while any relevant mapping remains `New`.
